sql:
SELECT order_id
FROM orders
WHERE status = 'delivered';

SELECT SUM(amount) AS total_revenue
FROM orders
WHERE channel = 'Amazon' AND STRFTIME('%Y', order_date) = '2022';

SELECT b2b_name, company_address
FROM b2b_customers
WHERE b2b_id = '1';

SELECT COUNT(o.order_id) AS order_count
FROM orders o
JOIN month m ON o.order_date LIKE m.month_name || '-' || m.year;

external_knowledge:
- "towering giants" metaphorically refers to the top B2B customers;
- "financial value of orders" corresponds to the total order value;
- "most significant" indicates the order value rank based on descending order of total order value;
- B2B stands for business-to-business transactions.
